HEADWORD: Quantitative
<hw>Quan"ti*ta*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>quantitatif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Relating to quantity.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Quan"ti*ta*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Quantitative analysis</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>analysis which determines the amount or quantity of each ingredient
of a substance, by weight or by volume; -- contrasted with
<contr>qualitative analysis</contr>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quantitive</ent>⟦br⟧
